comments.message:
Should have noted this in the previous review, but the OpenBMC coding conventions call for braces even when it is a one line statement.

https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/cpp-style-and-conventions.md#bracket-style

I think this is a good convention because it avoids the following class of hard to spot bugs:

  if (foo == 1)
    doFoo();
  else
    doBar();
    doBaz();   // Added later by different programmer being careless

or worse
  if (foo == 1)
    if (bar == 2)
      doBar();
      doBaz();   // This is actually in the first if's scope
